PLAYER_OF_THE_SEASON.notes: Liverpool's commanding centre-half helped the Reds to their highest-ever PL points total, and contributed to 20 clean sheets.

PLAYER_OF_THE_MONTH.notes: The Liverpool centre-back dominated at the back throughout December with four clean sheets and 29 headers won.

YNG_PLAYER_OF_THE_SEASON.notes: The inaugural award went to the Liverpool full-back after 13 assists and four goals in a title-winning 2019/20 campaign.

PLAYER_OF_THE_MONTH.notes: A goal, three assists and three clean sheets for the Liverpool right-back in December.
Liverpool right-back claimed the award after one goal, four assists and two clean sheets.

PLAYER_OF_THE_SEASON.notes: Liverpool’s Mohamed Salah broke the 38-match record for goals in a single campaign, with 32.

GOAL_OF_THE_MONTH.notes: Salah finished off a sensational counter-attacking goal at West Ham in a 3-1 win for Liverpool.
Salah won for the award for a brilliant solo effort v Man City at Anfield (3 October).

PLAYER_OF_THE_MONTH.notes: The Egyptian claimed his first PL award thanks to seven league goals from four matches for Liverpool.
Salah's second award of the season came via four goals and two assists from three matches for Liverpool.
Salah became the first player to win three Player of the Month awards in one season after netting six times in March.
Liverpool's Egyptian produced five goals and four assists in a sensational October.
